ss, simple statistical analysis favors the clear atmosphere scenario.\nA larger wavelength coverage or space-based data is required to characterize\nthe constituents of Qatar-1b's atmosphere and to compare it to the well known\nHD 189733b. On top of the similarities of the orbital and physical parameters\nof both exoplanets, from a long Halpha photometric follow-up of Qatar-1,\npresented in this work, we find Qatar-1 to be as active as HD 189733.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 30 Mar 2017 19:40:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-07-05"}
